sub_title: Certified Cross-Cultural Trainer/consultant/ coach/ author Founder Between2Cultures
summary:
"Sharing what I know to help people grow" 
Inspiring & energetic certified Cross-Cultural trainer| coach| author helping managers & global teams understand the essentials of working across cultures and equip them with critical strategies and knowledge to work effectively across cultures. 
My 'Go To' area
	Intercultural communication
	Working with India/ Indians
	Working with the Dutch
	Bridging Asia and the Netherlands
	Understanding the Non- Western perspective

COACH& TRAINER
I am a certified intercultural trainer (The interchange Institute Washington DC), author, coach and founder Between2Cultures, with a passion for people and diversity. Through my culture training's I help teachers, managers and multinational teams master, tangible inter cultural competence that will enable them to connect with their colleagues work successfully with confidence with other cultures. Thus boosting productivity, creativity and innovation.
WORKING WITH DIVERSITY
My training's are built upon my 40 years of experience of having lived and worked with diversity in the East and the West..
Born in Nepal, brought up in India in an international environment. Traveled intensively and now living in The Netherlands for over 28 years. And having worked as a policy officer for the Dutch government for 17 years. I am an experienced professional in living and working between cultures.         
Lecturer
I was asked to be a lecturer at the university of Fontys in The Netherlands to provide lectures to international students on, Dutch culture and language. I also provided Intercultural awareness and communication training and workshops to the students and university teachers and staff. With regard to internationalization. 
AUTHOR
My book, ‘Dutch-ess from the Himalayas’  which did catch the eye of the local newspaper and the National Dutch radio also interviewed me. Is written to inspire people living and working between cultures. My second book (Dutch), ‘Wanneer culturen elkaar ontmoeten’ is a result of 25 years of research, and provides my readers with the key to working successfully with other cultures. 

‘Sharing what I know to help people grow ‘ with this motto I create an environment where people are motivated and inspired to master the skills that to navigate cultures and be culturally efficient, while interacting with any culture.
WHAT MAKES ME 'ME'?
 Inspiring, energetic, proactive, creative, client goal-oriented, culture sensitive, sincere and team player.
Speak 6 languages: bilingual in English and Dutch, both professional level.

In 2006 heeft Het Lijnt een facelift gekregen. Dankzij de genomen maatregelen hebben de randen van dit bosgebied een geleidelijke overgang van bos naar landbouw.
